      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-03-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-07-28T15:52:18Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Voting Only Through English Act or the VOTE Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill requires states to use English-only ballots to qualify for certain federal election funds. It also repeals a prohibition on English-only federal elections and eliminates language assistance provisions under the Voting Rights Act of 1965 (VRA). (The VRA requires&amp;nbsp;some jurisdictions to provide materials such as ballots and registration information in English and in other covered languages for voters whose English proficiency is limited. The bill removes these requirements.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill&amp;nbsp;prohibits a state from receiving federal election administration funds if the state provides ballots for a federal election that include text in any language other than English.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
